Trading system:
    Players can trade goods between each other.
    This would make bartering with players more effective than it would normally be with dropping items and money.
    Players can initiate a trade by pressing use key on them and pressing the "Trade" button that shows up.
    Players who receive trade request can either accept or deny.
    Trade range: 120hu

    If it's denied:
        The player cannot send trade request to the target for the next 30 seconds.
    If it's accepted:
        The trade starts, and the trade menu pops up.

        At any time, if the player is too far away, or is not alive, the popup closes and the trade is cancelled automatically.
        Everything is networked real-time, this includes offered items and money.
        



